# Content Management

## Content Structure

- Portfolio content is stored in [src/assets/content.json](mdc:src/assets/content.json)
- Content includes email, headline, and paragraph with HTML support
- Content is imported directly into React components

## Content Fields

- `email`: Contact email address
- `headline`: Main portfolio headline/title
- `paragraph`: Detailed description with HTML markup support

## Content Usage

- Content is imported in [src/App.tsx](mdc:src/App.tsx) as a JSON module
- HTML content is rendered using `dangerouslySetInnerHTML`
- Links in content open in new tabs with `target="_blank"`

## Content Updates

- Modify [src/assets/content.json](mdc:src/assets/content.json) to update portfolio content
- HTML is supported in the paragraph field for rich formatting
- Email links are automatically generated with mailto: protocol

## Font Assets

- Custom fonts are stored in [src/assets/fonts/](mdc:src/assets/fonts/)
- Gotham font family with multiple formats (otf, woff, woff2)
- Fonts are loaded through CSS imports
  description:
  globs:
  alwaysApply: false

